    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a massive park factor boost (+14%) and a favorable matchup against Feltner; his ability to pair elite power with consistent production makes him the anchor of our lineup. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an elite order spot and dynamic platoon advantage, though we are tracking the risk posed by the opposing battery\u2019s hold efficiency, which slightly dampens his stolen base upside. The core of our lineup is further bolstered by **Andy Pages**, whose score of 75.64 is largely driven by his favorable matchup against the slow delivery of the opposition, granting him an ideal environment to exploit the base paths.\n\nOur bench optimization was particularly difficult today, as **Nasim Nunez** (60.21) fell just short of the active roster. While **Nasim Nunez** offers the elite sprint speed we value for our stolen base-starved categories, the cumulative efficiency scores of our starters\u2014specifically the high-upside matchup for **Josh Lowe** (72.21)\u2014pushed him to the pine. We are monitoring **Jackson Merrill**\u2019s status closely, as his \"Lineup Pending\" designation introduces risk; should he drop out of the #3 spot or miss the game entirely, we are prepared to pivot to more reliable assets. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Luis Robert Jr.** (57.07), whose score is currently dragged down by a negative platoon adjustment, making him our most volatile start against Taillon. We continue to hold high-upside prospects like **Coby Mayo**, **Jordan Westburg**, and **Josh Jung** in reserve, waiting for the right situational alignment to deploy them in future rotations.",
